@arjun4084346 BTW, this seems related to the issue I opened: [GOBBLIN-318](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GOBBLIN-318)

There seems to be an underlying issue in Helix or the client -> Helix communication that should actually be solved.  This PR can mitigate the issue, but won't actually solve it.

@arjun4084346 One question is, does the client (in this case a Worker node) retry calls to helix that fail (basically zk operations)?
